{"annotations": [{"id": ["mesh:D016604"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "AFB1", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9980216026306152, "span": {"begin": 39, "end": 43}}, {"id": ["mim:278150", "mesh:D007039"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "AHF", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9937166571617126, "span": {"begin": 108, "end": 111}}, {"id": ["mesh:D009369"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "neoplastic lesions", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9992364048957825, "span": {"begin": 180, "end": 198}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:9817"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Keap1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9978050589561462, "span": {"begin": 277, "end": 282}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4780"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Nrf2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9987439513206482, "span": {"begin": 283, "end": 287}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ARE", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.8293359279632568, "span": {"begin": 288, "end": 291}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7157"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "p53", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9969063401222229, "span": {"begin": 316, "end": 319}}, {"id": ["mesh:D009369"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "tumor", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999874830245972, "span": {"begin": 417, "end": 422}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7471"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "Wnt", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9925475716590881, "span": {"begin": 497, "end": 500}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:1499"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "b-catenin", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9912837743759155, "span": {"begin": 501, "end": 510}}, {"id": ["mesh:D009369"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cancer", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999943971633911, "span": {"begin": 576, "end": 582}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "DNA", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.5912885069847107, "span": {"begin": 684, "end": 687}}, {"id": ["mesh:D009369"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cancer", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999879598617554, "span": {"begin": 751, "end": 757}}], "text": "There is no direct evidence addressing AFB1 induced critical gene mutations and the subsequent induction of AHF.  However, in general the progression from chemical exposure to pre-neoplastic lesions appears to include six general mechanisms: 1) decrease in the activity of the Keap1/Nrf2/ARE pathway; 2) decrease in p53 function leading to increased survival in the presence of genomic instability; 3) changes in the tumor microenvironment within cells; 4) alterations in apoptosis; 5) changes in Wnt/b-catenin signaling, and 6) gene expression changes that may be related to cancer promotion/progression. [24-36]   In addition to these six possible mechanisms, epigenetic changes in DNA methylation may occur and may be related to the progression of cancer. [37-41]", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:40:17 +0000 2026"}